	<recipe>
		<title>Meatballs</title>
		<preptime>10 min</preptime>
		<cooktime>10 min</cooktime>
		<totaltime>20 min</totaltime>
		<description>
			Tasty Swedish Meatballs
		</description>
		<ingredient>

								<li>1 pound lean ground beef</li>
								<li>2 cloves garlic chopped</li>
								<li>2 tablespoons diced onion</li>
								<li>1 large egg</li>
								<li>1/2 teaspoon salt</li>
								<li>1/2 teaspoon ground black pepper</li>
								<li>2 tablespoons bread or cracker crumbs</li>
								<li>2 tablespoons chopped fresh parsley (optional)</li>
								<li>olive oil</li>

		</ingredient>
		<recipetext>
									<li>Combine beef, veal, and pork in a large bowl. Add garlic, eggs, cheese, parsley, salt and pepper.</li>
									<li>Blend bread crumbs into meat mixture. Slowly add the water 1/2 cup at a time. The mixture should be very moist but still hold its shape if rolled into meatballs.</li>
									<li>Heat olive oil in a large skillet. Fry meatballs in batches.</li>
									<li>Remove the meatballs from the skillet or saute pan and drain on a plate lined with paper towels.</li>
		</recipetext>
